# Global extrema

%%visits: 2
Finding the global extrema
    - find all $c_1,c_2,\ldots \in [a,b]$ where $f'(c_k) = 0$ (also second derivate if there are too many minima)
    - evaluate $f(c_k) \forall k$
    - evaluate $f(a),f(b)$
    - select the maximal value from the list $f(a),f(b),f(c_1),f(c_2)$
    
